        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 5:04PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 504 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Nantahala Lake, or 11 miles east of Hayesville, moving west at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hayesville, Nantahala Lake, Shooting Creek, Tusquitee, and Brasstown.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
